# UPSTREAMS FILE
#
# Use one line per upstream using the following (URL) syntax:
#
# <protocol>://<hostname|ip>[:<port>][/<path>}[#<bootstrap-ip>]
#
# <protocol>: The protocol to be uses, we have the following variants:
#
#             udp  : classic DNS over UDP (default port UDP 53)
#             tcp  : classic DNS over TCP (default port TCP 53)
#             tls  : DNS over TLS, you can also use "dot" (default TCP port 853)
#             doh  : DNS over HTTPS (http/1.1 and http/2), you can also use "https" (default TCP port 443)
#             doq  : DNS over QUIC, you can also use "quic" (default UDP port 853)
#             doh3 : DNS over HTTP/3, you can also use "h3" (default UDP port 443):
#
# <hostname|ip>: The hostname or IP of the upstream server.
#
# <port>: The port of the upstream server to use, when omitted, the default will be used.
#
# <path>: The DOH/DOH3 path to be used, when omitted the default "/dns-query" will be used.
#
# <bootstrap-ip>: The IP of the upstream server to use. This prevents (unencrypted) lookups of the <hostname>.


